# Grammar for Qwen3-style models served behind Pi (or any client using a
# qwen-chat-template provider that sets `chat_template_kwargs.enable_thinking`).
#
# The chat template injects "<think>\n" before the assistant's first token,
# so the model's actual emitted output starts with the slot content.
# This grammar:
#
#   1. Constrains the reasoning scratchpad to a 3-slot IR
#      (STATE / ACTION / EXPECT)
#   2. Requires "</think>\n" to terminate the reasoning block
#   3. Leaves everything after </think> permissive so the model is free
#      to emit native tool-call XML (which SGLang's qwen3_coder parser
#      then converts into OpenAI tool_calls for the client)
#
# Same principle as the blog grammars: constrain the scratchpad, free the
# answer. Each rule MUST be on a single line for llama.cpp's GBNF parser.

root ::= "STATE: " line "ACTION: " line "EXPECT: " line "</think>\n" rest
line ::= [^\n]+ "\n"
rest ::= [\x09\x0A\x0D\x20-\x7E]*
